snippet.textDisplay: Short Fan-Fact from Germany. Writen in the Newsletter "Rheinische Post":SWAT units climb Cologne Cathedral January 11, 2018 at 12:55 PMWith team spirit and fitness, Special Operations Commands train for the fight against terrorism. For four days, a comparative competition under the name "Coloniale" will take place in Cologne, in which SEK officials from Bielefeld, Dortmund, Düsseldorf, Essen, Munich, Münster, Rhineland-Palatinate, Rotterdamm, Zurich as well as special units of the Customs Criminal Office will take part. Lutz Flassnöcker, spokesman for the Cologne Police, said: "Of course it is also about training togetherness. On Wednesday, units climbed the 157-metre-high north tower of Cologne Cathedral. "Cologne Cathedral is also a potential target for attacks in this day and age. But that doesn't mean that we have currently identified the cathedral as a specific point of attack," says Flassnöcker.-----------------------------------------Competitions between special forces are real and normal, but receive little attention in the press

Several major media outlets in Finland gave front-page coverage on a forum discussing forced organ harvesting in China held in Helsinki on September 19, 2019. Finland’s most popular newspapers, the Helsinki Daily (Helsingin Sanomat) and HSL (the top Swedish newspaper in Finland), reported on the forum.

The reason for the rise of organ transplantation in China, the response of the international community, and people’s indignation at the Chinese Communist Party’s (CCP) state-sanctioned organ harvesting from living Falun Gong practitioners were all discussed during the forum.
